text: Francis James (1559–1616), of Wells and Bristol, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Dorchester in 1593, for Corfe Castle in 1597, for Minehead in 1601 and for Wareham in 1604. His brother, William James, was bishop of Durham. ==References== Category:1559 births Category:1616 deaths Category:People from Wells, Somerset Category:People from Bristol Category:Members of the Parliament of England for Dorchester Category:English MPs 1593 Category:English MPs 1597–1598 Category:English MPs 1601 Category:English MPs 1604–1611
